thread.title: UH soccer team routed at Cal State Fullerton
thread.title_full: UH soccer team routed at Cal State Fullerton - Hawaii News - Honolulu Star-Advertiser

author: Star-Advertiser staff
title: UH soccer team routed at Cal State Fullerton
text:
The Hawaii soccer team continued to struggle in a 4-0 loss at Cal State Fullerton this afternoon. Last-place UH fell to 0-4 in Big West Conference play and 3-10-1 overall.
With the loss, the Rainbow Wahine's chances of qualifying for the Big West tournament (a top-four finish is required) are slim with four games to play.
UH trailed just 1-0 at halftime after a goal by Rebecca Wilson, but Wilson would score twice more in the second half to complete the hat trick and Ivy Diego scored on an assist by Wilson.
The Rainbow Wahine have been outscored 16-3 in four Big West Games. They were outshot 26-10 today.
The Rainbow Wahine return home for a single-game week, against CSUN next Sunday.
